      <abstract>Soldier from Detroit, Mich., captain of Co. A, 339th U.S. Infantry who served in the Allied intervention in Russia, 1918-1920, the "Polar Bear Expedition." Collection includes letters from Edmund Ironside, commanding officer of the Allied expedition and miscellaneous citations and decorations concerning activities of the Polar Bear expedition; also photographs.</abstract>
      <unitid countrycode="us" repositorycode="MiU-H" encodinganalog="099" type="call number">86617 Aa 1</unitid>
      <langmaterial>The materials are in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English.</language></langmaterial>
      <repository>
        <corpname encodinganalog="852"><subarea>Bentley Historical Library</subarea> University of Michigan</corpname>
        <extptr href="bhladd" show="embed" actuate="onload"/>
      </repository>
    </did>
    <descgrp type="admin">
      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
        <p>The collection was donated by the Polar Bear Association, in 1964 (Donor no.: <num type="donor" encodinganalog="541$e">4145</num>).</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict encodinganalog="506">
        <p>The collection is open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite encodinganalog="524">
        <p>item, folder title, box no., Otto Arthur Odjard papers, Bentley Historical Library, University of Michigan</p>
      </prefercite>
    </descgrp>
    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Resident of <geogname normal="Detroit (Mich.)">Detroit</geogname>, served as captain, <corpname normal="United States. Army. Infantry, 339th. Company A.">Co. A, 339th Infantry</corpname>.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p><genreform normal="Letters (correspondence)">Letters</genreform> from <persname normal="Ironside, Edmund, Sir, 1880-1959.">Edmund Ironside</persname>, commanding officer of the Allied expedition and miscellaneous citations and decorations concerning activities of the <subject normal="Polar Bear Expedition.">Polar Bear expedition</subject>. Also a <genreform normal="Photographs.">photo</genreform> of <persname normal="Odjard, Otto Arthur.">Odjard</persname> with a group of children.</p>
    </scopecontent>
